&lt;b&gt;In Belarus, the Orthodox opposition member Sergei Tichanovskiy has been released&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 21, it became known about the release of &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://belarus2020.churchby.info/tihanovskij-sergej/&quot;&gt;Sergei Tichanovskiy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; — a Christian, blogger and one of the most famous political prisoners of Belarus. He became one of 14 people released shortly after the visit to Minsk of Donald Trump&#x27;s special representative Keith Kellogg.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tichanovskiy is the author of the YouTube channel &quot;A Country for Life&quot; and the husband of Svetlana Tichanovskaya, who was called the winner of the 2020 presidential election. The authorities accused him of &quot;organizing mass riots&quot;, &quot;inciting hatred&quot; and &quot;obstructing electoral rights&quot;. In December 2021, he was sentenced to 18 years in a high-security colony.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sergei openly declared his Orthodox faith and repeatedly said that his struggle is for truth, justice and dignity.&lt;/p&gt;

