&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;The released Belarusian opposition figure expressed support for Zelenskyy.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A live broadcast of a press conference is currently underway with the participation of Sergei Tikhanovsky, the leader of the 2020 opposition, who was sentenced by the Lukashenko regime to 18 years in prison and was released yesterday.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tikhanovsky says that he is an Orthodox Christian, but he was not allowed to see a priest, visit the prison church, confess, or receive communion. He was even denied basic things allowed for prisoners - for several years he was in absolute isolation, without the possibility of correspondence. His mail was not delivered to him.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When asked about his visit to Crimea after 2014, Sergei Tikhanovsky explained that this trip was related to a pilgrimage to Saint Luke of Crimea, and he did not attach much importance to it at the time. Now he has expressed absolute support for Volodymyr Zelenskyy. He claims that the President of Ukraine has to bear much more than he did while in a Belarusian prison. He called Zelenskyy his hero.&lt;/p&gt;

#belarus #orthodox

[Channel] &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/shaltnotkill&quot;&gt;Christians against the war!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;During today&#x27;s press conference with the released political prisoners, Sergei Tikhanovsky spoke about his faith.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;He said that he is an Orthodox Christian, but in custody he was not allowed to exercise his legal right to practice his religion:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;For more than 5 years, they did not let me confess. Imagine, an Orthodox Christian is not allowed to confess or take communion. The law says: every month. In the pre-trial detention center, in prison. Every month. No letters, no phone calls, no priest, no lawyers - nothing.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regarding his attitude towards Putin:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Our common enemy is the Putin regime. Until it collapses there, there can be no victory in Belarus. Putin said that black is white. He chose his candidate in Belarus in 2020. And he still calls himself an Orthodox believer. But he calls black white.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regarding his visit to Crimea after 2014:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;I am an Orthodox Christian. One year, a friend invited me to go on a pilgrimage trip for one or two days. At that time I was working in Moscow. This friend of mine is a philanthropist. He invited me to [St. Luke of Crimea], a saint. He was arranging an arch there at his own expense. An entrepreneur. He invited me - I didn&#x27;t have the opportunity to go anywhere special at that time. And I went with him for one day. Including to meet the former abbot of our Zhirovichi Monastery. The abbot was in Crimea at that time. He is my spiritual father. We came, stayed overnight with the spiritual father. And we went to the holy sites. At that time, while living and working in Russia, to take a pilgrimage trip - I treated it that way. I didn&#x27;t think: ours, yours, something else. I just didn&#x27;t think about it at all. I wasn&#x27;t involved in politics, I wasn&#x27;t a blogger. I was an ordinary citizen, an ordinary Belarusian. We went there in 2011 and I didn&#x27;t think it could be perceived in any way. Crimea is Ukrainian territory. And I absolutely do not support Russia&#x27;s claims.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/christianvision&quot;&gt;Christian Vision: NOT TO WAR!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&quot;The main thing is not to let the prison into you&quot; - the words of the political prisoner Catholic helped others&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At today&#x27;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cN99Dal-xww&quot;&gt;press conference&lt;/a&gt;, two released political prisoners &lt;b&gt;Igor Karney&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;Sergey Sheleh&lt;/b&gt; said that they were inspired by the words of their cellmate, a Catholic, a teacher of the Catechism &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://belarus2020.churchby.info/beloded-vladislav/&quot;&gt;Vladislav Beloded&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

Source channel: &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/christianvision&quot;&gt;Christian Vision: NO TO WAR!&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;The head priest of the Russian Orthodox Church sees no point in meeting with Ukrainian prisoners of war&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ukrainian prisoners of war report torture in Russia, many of them return home as a result of exchanges exhausted and emaciated. But the chief military priest of the Russian Orthodox Church, &lt;b&gt;Dmitry Vasilenko&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://rtvi.com/stories/molitsya-o-vragah-glavnyj-batyushka-svo-o-russkih-i-ukrainczah-vojne-i-mire/&quot;&gt;sees no point&lt;/a&gt; in meeting with them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&quot;Why should I meet with them? This is not my task. Of course, I have met, seen and know, but this is not my main task. There are special services that deal with them. If we are asked, we are ready to help. There are priests who are specifically engaged in this, who have experience working with prison inmates. But I have had to work with former Ukrainian servicemen fighting on our side. And prisoners are a more secondary task. I have enough work with ours, with those who are fighting.&quot;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The priest considers Ukrainians to be part of the &lt;i&gt;&quot;single Russian people,&quot;&lt;/i&gt; but this does not prevent him from blessing their killings: &lt;i&gt;&quot;they were zombified and turned into mankurts, knowing neither people nor tribe, not realizing.&quot;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

